dataset = ["\nDear Mr./Ms. Joseph,\nI am pleased to extend the following offer of employment to you on behalf of [insert your company’s name] You have been selected as the best candidate for the [insert job position name] position. Congratulations!\nWe believe that your knowledge, skills and experience would be an ideal fit for our [insert your company's department] team. We hope you will enjoy your role and make a significant contribution to the overall success of Company.\nPlease take the time to review our offer. It includes important details about your compensation, benefits and the terms and conditions of your anticipated employment with Company.\n", '\nSubject: Annual leave application\n\nDear Arun,\n\nI am writing this email with reference to my remaining annual leave quota. I am planning to go on a trip to Europe with my family. Thus, I would like to avail my remaining 25 days of annual leave from 05/12/2020 to 10/12/2020\n\nI have assigned my duties to ( name of a team member) for the current project we are working on. He/She has been working with me and understands the role effectively. Also, I am looking for all the essential inputs required for the project before I leave for the vacation.\n\nI request you to consider my leave request. During my absence, I can be reached at my phone number and email id ak@gmail.com. \n\nYours sincerely\n', '\nSubject: sample letter for the insurance claim\n\nDear Sir/ Madam,\n\nI am Govind writing this letter to you to grab your attention to the unsettled issue of my insurance claim. I had bought an insurance of my car which had an accident yesterday. The insurance enables me to ask for a claim. Your customer service center has promised me a reply but they have failed to do so.\n\nI request you to see what the matter is and reply at the earliest. Looking forward to your kind co-operation.\n\nThanking you,\n\nYours sincerely,\n', '\nDear John,\n\nWe were all very excited to meet and get to know you over the past few days. We have been impressed with your background and would like to formally offer you the position of manager. This is a full time position. You will be reporting to the head of the Department department. [If applicable: Please note that Company_name is an at-will employer. That means that either you or Company_name are free to end the employment relationship at any time, with or without notice or cause.]\n', '\nSubject: Maternity leave application\n\nDear Sir\n\nI am Kavya working as a Assistant Manager in Finance Department. \n\nI am nearing the end of my pregnancy and hence seeking maternity leave as suggested by my doctor. I request you to kindly approve my maternity leave for the duration of 05/12/2020 to 05/6/2021 as per company policy. My due date is (date). \n\nAs I will be away for a continued long period, I have assigned my duties and responsibilities to (colleague name). In case of any difficulty, you can reach out to me at my number 232323232.\n\nI have attached my medical certificate along with pregnancy proof submission and other relevant documents. Apart from this, I would also like to understand the insurance coverage for cashless billing process. Please let me know the concerned person for the same.\n\nThank you for your consideration.\n', '\nSubject – sample letter for the insurance claim\n\nDear Sir /Madam,\n\nThis letter is concerning the claim of insurance for my car. I have an insurance policy for my car, and the insurance number is 195846. My car had an accident yesterday. I was about to park my car near my office, and a truck came from behind and accidentally hit my car from the back side. As a result, the back portion of the car is damaged badly.\n\nWhen the incident took place, I immediately contacted the customer support and gave them all the information related. I have gone through my insurance papers and came to know that I can get a claim. Your company has directed an executive and got one report done and replied to me that they will contact me concerning the insurance and will give the reply from the company as soon as possible.\n', '\nDear Akhil,\n \nCongratulations on your offer from Company Name! We are delighted to offer you the position of Job Title with an anticipated start date of 20/12/2020.\n \nAs discussed, please find attached your detailed offer letter. If you choose to accept this offer, please sign, scan, and email your letter to me at email@email.com by 12/12/2020.\n \n \nIn the meantime, please don’t hesitate to reach out to me, either through email or by calling me directly at 00000000 if you should have any questions or concerns.\n \nWe are looking forward to hearing from you and hope you’ll join our team!\n', '\nSubject: Casual leave application\n\nDear Sir\n\nI am writing to request you for a five-day leave from (start date) to (end-date) as I have to urgently attend a medical emergency of a close relative and as he/she is situated in Delhi, I have to be away from the town for five days. \n\nI will resume work from 12/12/2020, and I shall be reachable at my email id (email address) and phone number (contact number). Besides, I have instructed (colleague name) to take care of certain responsibilities during my absence. She/He is well equipped for any emergency or in case any assistance is required.\n\nYours Sincerely,\n\n', '\nDear Sir,\n\nThis is regarding the insurance claim for my car. My policy number is 000000.\n\nThe details of the accident are as given below:\n\nI parked my vehicle in the parking area at my office. Unfortunately, a delivery truck tried to park between two cars and hit my car from behind. The body from behind got smashed.\n\nWhen I realized I immediately contacted your customer care and gave the details. I checked all my Insurance papers and realized that I am eligible for a claim of 250000. Your Company sent a representative and filed the report, and they told that they will call me soon regarding the insurance and will get the feedback from the company at the earliest.\n\nI would like to bring to your notice that I didn’t get any correspondence from the company yet in spite of my reminders for the last ten days.\n\nKindly look into it and expecting a positive response at the earliest.\n\nThanking you,\n', '\nDear George,\nCongratulations on your offer from Company Name! We are delighted to offer you the position of Job Title with an anticipated start date of 20/12/2020.\n\nThis is a full time position. You will be reporting to the head of the Department department.\nWe are looking forward to hearing from you and hope you’ll join our team!', '\nSubject: Vacation leave application\n\nSir\n\nThis is to request you for your approval for a ten-day leave for my planned trip to Kerela with my family. I have been collecting my leaves for the trip, and I am very excited about the same. \n\nI am writing this letter to formally notify you about my leaves from 10/12/2020 to 20/12/2020. I will join office from Monday, i.e. on (date).\n\nI will update you with the final draft this week and will submit the file to you. You can contact Hema in my absence as she is aware of the same. I can be reached at email id iam@gmail.com and phone number 12121212121 in case of any queries.\n\nI hope you will acknowledge my application and process the same earliest. \n\nThank You\n', '\nDear Sir,\n\nThis is regarding the insurance claim for my car. \nI was about to park my car near my office, and a truck came from behind and accidentally hit my car from the back side. As a result, the back portion of the car is damaged badly.\nKindly look into it and expecting a positive response at the earliest.\n']

